waffle
------------------------------------------
Waffle is a cross-platform library that allows one to defer selection of an
OpenGL API and of window system until runtime. For example, on Linux, Waffle
enables an application to select X11/EGL with an OpenGL 3.3 core profile,
Wayland with OpenGL ES2, and other window system / API combinations.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.4-1
  libEGL-devel-19.1.6-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-1
  libGL-devel-19.1.6-1
  libwaffle-devel-1.6.1-1bl1
  libwaffle0-1.6.1-1bl1
  libX11-xcb-devel-1.6.9-1
  libX11-xcb1-1.6.9-1
  libX11_6-1.6.9-1
  libxcb1-1.14-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-1
  gcc-objc-9.3.0-1
  meson-0.53.2-1
  ninja-1.10.0-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.waffle-gl.org/

Canonical download:
  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/waffle/-/archive/v1.6.1/waffle-v1.6.1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack waffle-1.6.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./waffle-1.6.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/waffle-1.6.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/waffle-1.6.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libwaffle0-1.6.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libwaffle-devel-1.6.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

